    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://newyork.craigslist.org/que/ret/6036898702.html"></div>
        </div>
Locations: College Point / Flushing <br>
<br>
Love what you do, join our BEAUTIFUL team!<br>
<br>
Do you have a passion for beauty? Are you motivated to drive sales and have retail sales experience? Are you able to work independently in a retail setting to create an exciting and welcoming environment for customers? <br>
<br>
If so, you could be the next onsite Beauty Concierge within Target's beauty aisles. As a Beauty Concierge you are responsible for creating meaningful sales interactions with customers, educating and consulting consumers on beauty items across hair care, skincare and cosmetics.<br>
<br>
The Beauty Concierge role is like no other in that you are trusted to work independently within a Target location. You will have the full support of a manager through regular visits and in-store Skype meetings. You will be part of a growing movement that is changing the face of beauty in retail. For more information about Beauty Concierge, check out the following <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0auflb191H0&amp;feature=youtu.be" rel="nofollow">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0auflb191H0&amp;feature=youtu.be</a><br>
<br>
 "Guest Spotlighting" / Customer service skills<br>
•	Educate customers and make targeted beauty recommendations in a sales environment<br>
•	Ability to utilize samples and select demo products in aisles with guest<br>
•	Serve as cosmetics, skin care and hair care expert in the aisles<br>
•	Recommend and sell products to customers across multiple lines<br>
•	Proactively approach and engage customers within the beauty aisles<br>
•	Must be outgoing, positive, and provide friendly, informed beauty advice<br>
•	Enjoy working to create and maintain a beautiful environment for your customers to shop<br>
•	Guest-centric and excited to focus on customer needs and service<br>
•	Ability to communicate and interact with bilingual consumers<br>
<br>
Job responsibilities and expectations<br>
•	Work a set schedule of 20 hours to 40 hours per week<br>
•	Work weekdays, weekends and select holidays<br>
•	Excellent verbal communication and interpersonal skills are vital to success in this position<br>
•	Ability to work independently within an assigned location<br>
•	Expected to meet with manager regularly in store and/or via Skype<br>
•	Candidates must be Bilingual (Spanish)<br>
<br>
Education and industry requirements  <br>
•	High school diploma or equivalent required - Licensed beauty professions are preferred but not required<br>
•	Minimum of 1+ year of retail experience required - Beauty retail experience preferred but not required<br>
<br>
What we need from you!<br>
•	Candidates must have a strong passion for beauty <br>
•	Aptitude and competency for selling and superior guest service<br>
•	Cosmetics, skin care, or hair care product sales experience preferred <br>
•	High standards of personal appearance<br>
•	Impeccable work ethic<br>
•	High level of personal accountability<br>
•	Applicants must be highly organized, tech savvy, dependable and stylish<br>
•	Work on feet for long hours and ability to lift up to 25 lbs <br>
•	Applicant must have reliable transportation and a valid driver's license<br>
•	Take pride in your work, keeping the beauty aisles well-stocked, well-merchandised, and clean <br>
<br>
Beautiful perks of Beauty Concierge<br>
•	Competitive hourly wage with career growth opportunities<br>
•	Opportunity to work beauty events and execute in aisle demo experiences ranging from skincare, hair care, cosmetics and nail demonstrations<br>
•	Exclusive training program that is designed for both beginners and seasoned beauty professionals<br>
•	Beauty gratis is provided throughout the year to ensure that Beauty Concierge staff is educated in all categories <br>
•	Paid training provided by top brands that include product giveaways<br>
•	Prospect to be featured in Beauty Concierge videos and/or provide expert advice through social networks<br>
<br>
"On Call" Positions Available: <br>
•         Not quite ready to commit to a specific schedule? Become an "On Call" Beauty Advisor and you will have the opportunity to can cover shifts as needed.<br>
•         We are also seeking beauty demonstrators for weekend in-store events.  Must be comfortable performing product demonstrations with consumers and applying product across beauty categories including skin care, hair care and cosmetics. <br>
<br>
Ready to let your passion for beauty shine?<br>
•	Email resume, a few words on why you want to be a part of our team and photo (optional) to: beautynewyork@pinpointconnections.com<br>
•	Complete the optional questionnaire below and include in email submission<br>
•	Indicate your zip code and position you are applying for in the subject line of your submission<br>
•	If you do not have a resume, you may still apply. Please complete the below questionnaire. For your ease, copy and paste questions into an email body with your responses to the questions included.<br>
<br>
Beauty Concierge Questionnaire - OPTIONAL<br>
Section 1 - Basic Information<br>
1.	How many hours per week are you looking for?<br>
2.	What is your availability during the week (Mon/Tues/Weds/Thurs/Fri)? <br>
Indicate what days you are available - an example of a weekday shift may look like 12PM-8:30PM <br>
3.	Are you able to work every weekend?  Indicate what days you are available - an example of a weekend shift may look like 11AM-6PM<br>
4.	How many years of beauty experience do you have?<br>
5.	How many years of sales/retail experience do you have?<br>
6.	When are you available to start?<br>
7.	Your zip code and phone number ?<br>
Section 2 - Yes/No<br>
8.	Do you have reliable transportation?<br>
9.	Do you have a beauty license or certification? (Cosmetology/Esthetician/certified makeup artist) If yes, please explain certifications.<br>
10.	Do you have a beauty blog or have you done video tutorials (ie: You Tube)? If so, please provide the link(s) <br>
11.	Are you comfortable approaching consumers in retail settings?<br>
12.	Are you comfortable applying products and/or demoing?<br>
13.	Have you ever worked independently in a retail setting? If yes, please give an example<br>
14.	Are you physically able to work on your feet for 8 hours a day?<br>
15.	Are you bilingual (Spanish)?<br>
16.	Do you have basic level PC, iPad or tablet skills?<br>
17.	Have you ever had to complete tasks (reporting) using online software?<br>
Section 3 - Short Answer<br>
18.	Why do you want to be a Beauty Concierge?   <br>
19.	Detail out your sales and/or retail experience<br>
20.	Please rank how  familiar are you with the following beauty categories on a scale of 1-3, 1 being the most familiar - hair, skin, cosmetics.  <br>
21.	Why are you the best fit for this position?<br>
<br>
<br>
ABOUT PINPOINT<br>
If marketing were a football game, in-store is the "fourth and goal" moment. Pinpoint builds and manages winning teams of premium in-store brand advocates to ensure retailers and brands engage shoppers at the shelf, grow fans and ultimately drive sales.  Pinpoint is a Brand Connections company and is a full-service Retail Services and Shopper Marketing agency.<br>
<br>
